headlines.description: Devonte Graham had 23 points and seven assists, Malik Newman added 20 and No. 8 Kansas beat Oklahoma 104-74 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Graham leads No. 8 Kansas to 104-74 rout of Oklahoma

headlines.description: Freshman Lonnie Walker IV scored 19 points, hitting 5 of 7 from 3-point range, and his deep 3 gave Miami the lead for good as the Hurricanes rode a late 13-0 burst to a 77-74 Atlantic Coast Conference win over Notre Dame on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walker IV hits 5 3s, scores 19, Miami beats Notre Dame 77-74

video.headline: Canes beat Fighting Irish by three

headlines.description: Kevin Huerter scored 18 points and Maryland beat Northwestern 71-64 to snap a seven-game road losing streak on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maryland beats Northwestern 71-64 to stop road skid

headlines.description: Aaron Brennan scored six of his 18 points in the final two minutes and Evan Hall had his second consecutive double-double to help IUPUI beat Oakland 74-67 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brennan, Hall help IUPUI beat Oakland 74-67

headlines.description: Jordan Perkins had 13 points and 14 assists on Monday night and North Carolina Central beat Howard 83-66.
Grant Benzinger scored 20 points and powered a late run Monday to help Wright State get past Cleveland State 72-63 on the Raiders' senior night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Benzinger powers Wright State past Cleveland State 72-63

headlines.description: Drew Mc Donald had his 15th double-double of the season with 27 points and 12 rebounds to help Northern Kentucky beat Youngstown State 70-51 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: N. Kentucky pulls away late, beats Youngstown St. 70-51

headlines.description: Brandon Tabb scored 34 points before fouling out in overtime, Isaiah Bailey had 28 points, nine rebounds and 10 assists and Bethune-Cookman beat Morgan State 96-95 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bethune-Cookman beats Morgan State 96-95 in OT

headlines.description: Marquis Collins had 23 points, seven rebounds and four assists and Delaware State ended Division I's second-longest losing streak at 21 games with a 69-51 victory over Coppin State on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Delaware State ends Division I's 2nd-longest losing streak

headlines.description: Denzel Keyes scored 21 points on 9-of-14 shooting and grabbed nine rebounds to help North Carolina A&T beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 78-69 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Keyes, NC A&T beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 78-69

headlines.description: Kalin Fisher had 10 of his career-high 37 points in overtime and Hampton knocked off conference-leading Savannah State 114-102 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hampton beats Savannah State 114-102 in OT

headlines.description: Marcus Ottey and Dikembe Dixson had 20 points each and UIC held off Detroit Mercy for a 94-87 win on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UIC uses late run to beat Detroit Mercy 94-87

headlines.description: Derrik Jamerson Jr. scored 15 points to lead five Norfolk State players in double figures and the Spartans pulled away in the second half for a 76-62 win over South Carolina State on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamerson Jr. scores 15, Norfolk St. beats South Carolina St.

headlines.description: Jared Sam had 20 points and 12 rebounds as Southern defeated Alabama A&M 60-50 on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sam scores 20 to lead Southern over Alabama A&M 60-50

headlines.description: Dante Scott had a double-double and Jordan Evans scored all of his 14 points in the second half as Mississippi Valley State rallied to beat Prairie View A&M 76-71 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mississippi Valley State beats Prairie View A&M 76-71

headlines.description: Martaveous McKnight and Terrance Banyard scored 16 points each and Arkansas-Pine Bluff overcame an 18-point deficit to beat Texas Southern 62-61 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pine Bluff erases 18-point deficit, beats Texas Southern

headlines.description: Brevin Pritzl scored 20 points, including two 3s in overtime, and Ethan Happ led a defensive resurgence in the extra period to help Wisconsin beat Minnesota 73-63 in overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brevin Pritzl's 20 points help Badgers beat Gophers in OT

headlines.description: Jacoby Ross had 19 points, seven rebounds and six assists Monday night to help Alabama State beat Alcorn State 82-62.

nowFeed.headline: Gregg Marshall's Wichita State squad lost to Louisville in the 2013 Final Four after surrendering a double-digit lead in the second half. He said he's joked with Michigan coach John Beilein, who lost to Louisville in the title game, about a rematch. "I've already jokingly told Coach Beilein that we should be playing and calling it the 2013 national championship," Marshall told ESPN. "I mean, it would only matter to us."

nowFeed.headline: The Louisville men’s basketball program will have to vacate its 2013 NCAA title and 2012 Final Four appearance after the NCAA denied its appeal of what the school described as “draconian penalties” levied against the team. The NCAA Division I Infractions Appeals Committee also upheld the penalty that requires Louisville to return money received through conference revenue sharing for NCAA tournament appearances in 2012, '13, '14 and '15.

nowFeed.headline: Eighth-ranked Kansas leads Oklahoma 49-38 at the half behind 11 points from Malik Newman. Trae Young flashed some wizardry with his passing, dishing six assists, but he's 1-of-6 shooting for four points. Young has attempted just one 3-pointer, an errant 35-foot heave at the buzzer. Credit Devonte' Graham with most of the defensive pressure, but many of the Jayhawks, including center Udoka Azubuike, have pitched in to deny looks to Young.
